headline: Array completes sale of select spectrum assets to AT&T for $1.018 billion
summary: Array Digital Infrastructure, Inc.SM (NYSE: AD) (ArraySM) today announced the successful closing of the previously announced agreement with AT&T (NYSE: T) to sell a portion of the Company's retained spectrum licenses for total consideration of $1.018 billion.

headline: T-Mobile US (TMUS) Valuation Check After Recent Share Price Swings And Analyst Target Gap
summary: What T-Mobile US (TMUS) offers and where the stock stands now T-Mobile US (TMUS) has seen mixed share performance recently, with a 1 day return of about a 1.5% decline, but a small gain over the past month and a larger pullback across the past 3 months. Against that backdrop, the company reports annual revenue of about US$85.8b and net income of roughly US$11.9b, with both revenue and net income showing positive annual growth rates based on the latest figures provided.
